 He thought a bit more and added: 'But they don't know how to play.' 'What do you mean, they don't know?' said his wife with surprise. 'They were first-class actors.' Luzhin looked at her sideways and immediately averted his eyes, and there was something about this she did not like.

Suddenly she realized what was up and began to debate with herself, how to make Luzhin forget this unfortunate game of chess, which that fool of a director had seen fit to introduce for the sake of 'atmosphere.'



